data.title: Gastrolux!
data.text:
I'm coining a new term.  This is an excellent place to pamper your tummy, gastrolux!  

Delicious, inventive, exciting selections for foodies!  The only reason 5 stars hasn't been granted is because I usually leave hungry and have dropped a load of cash.  So, if you don't mind splurging to enjoy a few bites of heavenly bliss, this is the place for you.  Also, you better be invited to a private event or only have Wednesday evening available, because that's it folks.

data.title: What a treasure in Green Bay!  Imaginative, delicious, dining adventure
data.text: Down the street from the Wednesday Farmers Market, sophisticated cuisine awaits!  Craft cocktails with artisanal bitters tempt, small plates are exquisitely assembled with sustainable, local and handmade ingredients.  We began with the charcuterie platter, which was beautiful as well as delicious and satisfying.  Followed by Maine mussels in a spicy tomato broth with chunks of pork belly, pheasant meatballs in a root beer BBQ sauce, rounded out by golden beets with goat cheese.  We were too full for dessert, although they all sounded as amazing as the rest of the menu.
